32// The WasmInliner provides the core graph inlining machinery for Webassembly
33// graphs.
34class WasmInliner final : public AdvancedReducer {
35 public:
36 WasmInliner(Editor* editor, wasm::CompilationEnv* env,
37 WasmCompilationData& data, MachineGraph* mcgraph,
38 const char* debug_name,
39 ZoneVector<WasmInliningPosition>* inlining_positions,
40 wasm::WasmFeatures* detected)
41 : AdvancedReducer(editor),
42 env_(env),
43 data_(data),
44 mcgraph_(mcgraph),
45 debug_name_(debug_name),
46 initial_graph_size_(mcgraph->graph()->NodeCount()),
47 current_graph_size_(initial_graph_size_),
48 inlining_candidates_(),
49 inlining_positions_(inlining_positions),
50 detected_(detected) {}
51
52 const char* reducer_name() const override { return "WasmInliner"; }
53
54 // Registers (tail) calls to possibly be inlined, prioritized by inlining
55 // heuristics provided by {LexicographicOrdering}.
56 // Only locally defined functions are inlinable, and a limited number of
57 // inlinings of a specific function is allowed.
58 Reduction Reduce(Node* node) final;
59 // Inlines calls registered by {Reduce}, until an inlining budget is exceeded.
60 void Finalize() final;
61
62 static bool graph_size_allows_inlining(const wasm::WasmModule* module,
63 size_t graph_size,
64 size_t initial_graph_size);
65
66 private:
67 struct CandidateInfo {
68 Node* node;
69 uint32_t inlinee_index;
70 int call_count;
71 int wire_byte_size;
72
73 int64_t score() const {
74 // Note that the zero-point is arbitrary. Functions with negative score
75 // can still get inlined.
76
77 // Note(mliedtke): Adding information about "this call has constant
78 // arguments" didn't seem to provide measurable gains at the current
79 // state, still this would be an interesting measure to retry at a later
80 // point potentially together with other metrics.
81 const int count_factor = 2;
82 const int size_factor = 3;
83 return int64_t{call_count} * count_factor -
84 int64_t{wire_byte_size} * size_factor;
85 }
86 };
87
88 struct LexicographicOrdering {
89 // Returns if c1 should be prioritized less than c2.
90 bool operator()(CandidateInfo& c1, CandidateInfo& c2) {
91 return c1.score() < c2.score();
92 }
93 };
94
95 Zone* zone() const { return mcgraph_->zone(); }
96 CommonOperatorBuilder* common() const { return mcgraph_->common(); }
97 Graph* graph() const { return mcgraph_->graph(); }
98 MachineGraph* mcgraph() const { return mcgraph_; }
99 const wasm::WasmModule* module() const;
100
101 Reduction ReduceCall(Node* call);
102 void InlineCall(Node* call, Node* callee_start, Node* callee_end,
103 const wasm::FunctionSig* inlinee_sig,
104 SourcePosition parent_pos,
105 wasm::DanglingExceptions* dangling_exceptions);
106 void InlineTailCall(Node* call, Node* callee_start, Node* callee_end);
107 void RewireFunctionEntry(Node* call, Node* callee_start);
108
109 int GetCallCount(Node* call);
110
111 void Trace(Node* call, int inlinee, const char* decision);
112 void Trace(const CandidateInfo& candidate, const char* decision);
113
114 wasm::CompilationEnv* const env_;
115 WasmCompilationData& data_;
116 MachineGraph* const mcgraph_;
117 const char* debug_name_;
118 const size_t initial_graph_size_;
119 size_t current_graph_size_;
120 std::priority_queue<CandidateInfo, std::vector<CandidateInfo>,
121 LexicographicOrdering>
122 inlining_candidates_;
123 std::unordered_set<Node*> seen_;
124 std::unordered_map<uint32_t, int> function_inlining_count_;
125 ZoneVector<WasmInliningPosition>* inlining_positions_;
126 wasm::WasmFeatures* detected_;
127};
128
129} // namespace compiler
130} // namespace internal
131} // namespace v8
